Treat any Windows target like MSVC when selecting compiler-rt builtins.

Under the MSVC ABI `long double` is 64-bit, so the x87 80-bit / 128-bit
`long double` builtins (fixxfdi.c, floatuntixf.c, ...) must not be compiled.
compiler-rt's builtins CMakeLists only excludes those sources when CMake's
`MSVC` variable is set, which requires the clang-cl frontend. nixpkgs drives
the cross build with the GNU clang driver (`clang --target=...-windows-msvc`),
so CMake never sets `MSVC` and the build fails with `unknown type name
'xf_float'`. Treat any `WIN32` target the same as `MSVC` to exclude them.

--- a/pkgs/development/compilers/llvm/common/compiler-rt/default.nix
+++ b/pkgs/development/compilers/llvm/common/compiler-rt/default.nix
@@ -222,8 +222,12 @@
   postPatch =
     lib.optionalString (!stdenv.hostPlatform.isDarwin) ''
       substituteInPlace cmake/builtin-config-ix.cmake \
         --replace-fail 'set(X86 i386)' 'set(X86 i386 i486 i586 i686)'
     ''
+    + lib.optionalString stdenv.hostPlatform.isWindows ''
+      substituteInPlace lib/builtins/CMakeLists.txt \
+        --replace-fail 'if (NOT MSVC)' 'if (NOT MSVC AND NOT WIN32)'
+    ''
     + lib.optionalString (!haveLibc) (
       (lib.optionalString (lib.versions.major release_version == "18") ''
         substituteInPlace lib/builtins/aarch64/sme-libc-routines.c \
